                <p>
                    <lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi>
                </p>
                <p>                    
                    tirupuvaṉa-c-cakkaravattikaḷ <hi rend="grantha">śrī</hi>-rā<hi rend="grantha">ja</hi>rā<hi rend="grantha">ja</hi>-tēvaṟkku yāṇṭu <num value="22">2 <g type="numeral">10</g> 2</num>-vatu <hi rend="grantha">meṣa</hi>-nāyaṟṟu <hi rend="grantha">pūrva-pakṣa</hi>ttu <hi rend="grantha">pañcami</hi>yum putaṉ-kiḻamaiyum peṟṟa pūcattu nāḷ
                </p>
                <p>
                    Uyya-k-koṇṭār-vaḷanāṭṭu Uṭaiyār tiru-p-pāmpuram-uṭaiyār <gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/> āṉa <gap reason="lost" quantity="3" unit="character"/> pāṭṭaṭai <gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character"/> paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar nittal paṭikku Aricillāṟṟil tiru-mañcaṉam <unclear>tiru</unclear>kalattukkum Aim-patt-iru-c-ceṅkaḻaṉi-t tiru-p-paḷḷittāmattukkum Ivvūrilum piṟinta(ta) Ūrilum Ivar kāṇiyāṉa nilattum kaḷattum Uṭppaṭa piṭāri kōyilukku teṟkku na<unclear>t</unclear>ta<unclear>m</unclear> teṉkaraiyilk koṇṭu Araikkōl Akalattu pōkiṟa cā <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>vākkālukku
                    <lb n="2"/>vaṭa kuḷam ciṟutu tiruntu Uḷpaṭa nilam panta <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> Itil Ūr nīṅkiṉa Iṟaiyili nittalp paṭikku tiruceṅkaḻaṉi Iṭa Aṭatta <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> 5<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>m tirumañcaṉam Eṭuppānukku Aṭaitta <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> m <gap reason="illegible" quantity="2" unit="character"/><note>There are 2 symbols which may represent fractions: 1/4 and 1/32. But it is not very clear what it refers to.</note>m Innilattu Oṭṭā . Ikkōyilil peruḷūr kiḻavaṉ <unclear>Eḻun</unclear>taruḷivitta tirukāmakōṭṭamuṭaiya māmalaiyāṭṭi<unclear>yā</unclear>rkku Amutu paṭikku Uṭalāka
                </p>
                
